@startuml lf-mmi
' Lattice-Free MMI training: the numerator graph (correct transcript) and the
' denominator graph (phone loop + LM covering all hypotheses) each score the
' acoustic posteriors via forward-backward; the MMI objective is their difference,
' warmed up / stabilized by cross-entropy regularization. Matches
' build_numerator_graph / build_denominator_graph / lfmmi_loss / LfMmiConfig in
' src/training/lfmmi.rs (Povey et al. 2016).
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #BF360C
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.4
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
  FontColor #102027
  BorderColor #E65100
}

title <b>Lattice-Free MMI</b>\n<size:11><latex>L_{\text{MMI}} = -( \log P_{\text{num}}(x) - \log P_{\text{den}}(x) )</latex> ;  warm-started with cross-entropy (xent_regularize)</size>

rectangle "<b>Acoustic posteriors</b>\n<latex>\log P(\text{pdf} \mid \text{frame})</latex>  [<latex>T \times</latex> num_pdfs]" as X #E1BEE7

rectangle "<b>Numerator graph</b>\ncorrect transcript · HMM topology\nbuild_numerator_graph" as NUM #FFE0B2
rectangle "<b>Denominator graph</b>\nphone loop + phone-LM (all hypotheses)\nbuild_denominator_graph" as DEN #FFCC80

X -down-> NUM : forward-backward
X -down-> DEN : forward-backward

rectangle "<b><latex>\log P_{\text{num}}(x)</latex></b>\nscore of the reference path" as PNUM #C8E6C9
rectangle "<b><latex>\log P_{\text{den}}(x)</latex></b>\n<latex>\log \Sigma_y P(y \mid x)</latex>  (leaky-HMM smoothed)" as PDEN #C8E6C9

NUM -down-> PNUM
DEN -down-> PDEN

rectangle "<b>MMI objective</b>\n<latex>L = -(\log P_{\text{num}} - \log P_{\text{den}})</latex>" as MMI #FFB74D
PNUM -down-> MMI
PDEN -down-> MMI

rectangle "<b>Warmup / regularization</b>\n+ xent_regularize · <latex>L_{\text{xent}}</latex>\n+ l2_regularize · <latex>\|\text{out}\|^2</latex>\n+ leaky_hmm_coefficient" as REG #FFCDD2
MMI -down-> REG : interpolate

rectangle "<b>Gradients</b>\n<latex>\partial L / \partial(\text{acoustic scores})</latex>\nLfMmiGradients" as GRAD #ECEFF1
REG -down-> GRAD : backprop

note right of DEN
  The denominator covers <i>all</i> competing word/phone
  sequences, so the lattice never has to be generated
  explicitly — hence "lattice-free" (Povey et al. 2016).
end note

note right of REG
  Early in training the MMI signal is noisy; interpolating
  with frame-level cross-entropy (the warmup term) keeps
  optimization stable until the model is well-aligned.
end note
@enduml
